OL,3,GNEWSCChanges to BBC News channel output
OL,4,C"not recreating or competing with BBC
OL,5,CBreakfast"
OL,6,
OL,7,FIn the communication to staff,
OL,8,Fsenior/deputy editor, BBC News channel,
OL,9,FJoe O'Brien, said the change will
OL,10,F"offer choice to our UK audiences; we
OL,11,Fare not recreating or competing with
OL,12,FBBC Breakfast".
OL,14,FThere will be some simple stylistic
OL,15,Ftweaks to the current international
OL,16,Fearly morning programming. O'Brien said
OL,17,Fthe look and feel of the output will
OL,18,Fcontinue to evolve.
