OL,3,GNEWSCChanges to BBC News channel output
OL,4,C"not recreating or competing with BBC
OL,5,CBreakfast"
OL,6,
OL,7,FThe three hours of live programming
OL,8,Fwill "harness the global might of the
OL,9,FBBC's news gathering operation, to tell
OL,10,Fand break stories live".
OL,12,FThe range of stories will "reflect a
OL,13,Fbroad agenda that appeals to all:
OL,14,Fhealth, consumer, climate".
OL,16,FSally Bundock will present the 5am and
OL,17,F6am programmes, with Martine Croxall
OL,18,Fanchoring from 7am.
